description:
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for a Clerical Officer to join our Radiology team. This is for a part time position of 23.25 hours based on a 2 week pattern as shown below;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Week 1- Tuesday, Wednesday, Friday 8.30am-5pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Week 2- Wednesday, Friday 8.30-5pm, and Sunday 8am-4.30pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The primary role is to provide a comprehensive range of clerical duties to support their role within the department. This will include arranging appointments, providing a welcoming reception for patients, making appropriate arrangements to support the smooth running of the Radiology Department. You will also assist in the transfer of images and support the administration work within the PACS office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for somebody with the following skills/requirements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurate keyboard/ computer skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer care experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the ability to work under pressure and to tight deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be a team player&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of MEDWAY PAS/CRIS is desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Melissa Nilan Clerical Services Manager Email address m.nilan@nhs.net Telephone number 01623 622515 ext: 3580&lt;/p&gt;
